# Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv sou_env

# Activate virtual environment
source sou_env/bin/activate


python3 -c "import cv2, pyzbar, PIL, psutil, requests, numpy; print('All packages imported successfully')"

# Test the attraction system
python3 test_attractions.py

# Test camera
python3 camera_test_simple.py

# Run attraction scanner
python3 AttractionA.py



You can test with these sample ticket formats:
TICKET_A_001_2P - Valid for Attraction A (2 persons)
TICKET_AB_001_3P - Valid for Attraction A & B (3 persons)
TICKET_ABC_001_4P - Valid for all attractions (4 persons)
TICKET_B_001_2P - Invalid for Attraction A (should show red X)